readme:
Service Usage

The Create Person Record service is used to Create a Person Record (PID) within TRIPS.
TRIPS will NOT perform match using the given request data, A new record will be created and allocated a PID.

Service Behaviour

The consumer of this service invokes this service with persons bio details and travel document details to create a record in TRIPS. This service is used to force create a record of a person even if some of his details exists in TRIPS. For this service, TRIPS mandates the following:
Family Name
Birth Year
Sex
This service returns newly created PID in TRIPS to Consumer.

Service Variants

None

Service Dependencies

None

Service Composition

This service is a composite service.

Service Flow

An event is generated by the Service Consumer which invokes the Create Border System Person Identifier service on the ESB;
ESB Validate the request message sent by the consumer
ESB transforms the consumer request into TRIPS request which is a flat file and sends to TRIPS
TRIPS returns response to the ESB
ESB transforms the TRIPS response to Consumer response and returns to consumer.
Alternate Flow 1 (AF1)
The following alternate service flow depicts the execution path that takes place when the primary provider raises an error.
ESB transforms Provider Error returned by TRIPS into Enterprise Error Message.
ESB returns response with Enterprise Error payload.
Alternate Flow 2 (AF2)
If the service call was timeout, ESB should return SV355.MSG- E07 to the consumer.

Transformation

See DIMA_DCD d15 Service Specification SV355 - v0.1 Create Border System Person Identifier (TRIPS).xls

Service State Management Decisions

No state management required.
